This method will give the most accurate results because it allows scientists to observe the long-term effects of the new fish species on the lake's ecosystem. (A) Measuring oxygen levels in the lake for two months may not capture the full impact of the new fish species, as the effects may take longer to manifest.

(B) Checking the lake water for nutrient levels on one day is a snapshot in time and may not reflect the long-term changes that occur as a result of the new fish species.

(D) Observing the surface of the lake for signs of the new fish after one week is too short a time frame to capture the full impact of the new species and may not provide a comprehensive understanding of the ecosystem's response.
